  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2 - Promoting Progressive Tax for Inclusive Development All (PPTID)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Increased implementation of progressive tax policies and initiatives
2. Socially excluded groups are advocating tax reforms from regressive to progressive regime
3. Increased civil society&#x2019;s influence in progressive tax reform/formulation</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;Conduct a comprehensive research on how the current tax regime has contributed to increasing inequality in Ghana
&#x2022;Undertake a desk review on best practices on progressive tax systems and practices on widening the tax net.
&#x2022;Hold 7 separate policy engagement meetings with Parliament, Ministry Of Finance and the Ghana Revenue Authority
&#x2022;Identify and mobilize the various socially excluded groups &#x2013; (Youth entrepreneurs in start-up, market women, artisans, PWD, LEAP beneficiaries
&#x2022;Conduct 3 deliberative dialogues on tax policies with 150 members of identified socially excluded groups (sensitization and perspectives sharing).
&#x2022;Facilitate 3 policy engagements between identified socially excluded groups and duty bearers on progressive tax reforms.
&#x2022;Dissemination and circulation of information (2000 copies of two researches) on Ghana tax system (regressive) to CSOs.
&#x2022;Dissemination and circulation of information (highlights of research on Ghana tax system (regressive) through traditional and new media.
&#x2022;Facilitate CSOs voice for tax reforms through the tax justice network platform (2 meetings)
&#x2022;Sensitize 20 media practitioners (reporters, news editors and presenters) to enable them set tax justice agenda</narrative>
  </description>
